BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 2 (KCNA) -- Hwang Chang-yop, 
secretary of the C.C. [Central Committee], the Workers' Party of 
Korea, today met and had a friendly talk with a delegation of 
the Turkish Association for Friendship with the People of the 
DPRK led by Ali Kalan, deputy general secretary of the Workers' 
Party of Turkey and chairman of the association. 
  Present there was Chon Yon-ok, vice-chairperson of the 
Korean 
Society for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries and 
chairperson of the Korea-Turkey Friendship Association. 
  The head of the delegation said, "We are greatly encouraged 
by the Korean people's staunch struggle against imperialism, 
U.S. imperialism in particular." 
  "We will do our utmost to expand and develop friendly 
relations between the peoples of Korea and Turkey in various 
fields", he stated. 

